cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is about single-image depth estimation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel training strategy and convolutional neural network architecture, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of this task in advanced driver assistance systems and autonomous vehicles, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also mentions the use of deep CNNs, which is a common technique in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of regression problems, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
